In article <TLB.93Nov24132658@chardonnay.harvard.edu> tlb@chardonnay.harvard.edu (Trevor Blackwell) writes:
>You need to have _proof_, that for any chosen values of the seed, you
>will not end up with a short-length periodic sequence. 

This has always been bugging me.  If a system has cycles (short-length
periodic sequences bit-wise or block-wise) does it necessarily mean it 
is crytographically week - unless there is a predictability in the 
set of "week" keys themselves.

